Istanbul’s Grand Bazaar Raided in Fake Handbag Swoop, Vatan Says

-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 
2011-04-24T07:40:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-24/istanbul-s-grand-bazaar-raided-in-fake-handbag-swoop-vatan-says.html
Turkish police raided 30 stores in
Istanbul’s Grand Bazaar, seizing thousands of handbags alleged
to be copies of Gucci,  Louis Vuitton  and Christian Dior, Vatan
newspaper reported.  Hundreds of police were involved in the operation after a
six-month probe into who was distributing and selling the goods,
Vatan said. Police also searced 11 warehouses in the city where
they suspected the fake bags and purses were stored, Vatan said.  The raids followed a complaint from the  Association of
Registered Trademarks , which seeks to protect international
patent holders in  Turkey , the newspaper reported.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
